For Bella Manel (October 13, 1915 - April 3, 2010)

Bella was born in New York City. A pioneering woman in mathematics, she earned her PhD in 1939 from NYU, under the supervision of Richard Courant.  She worked for TRW in Hawthorne and at the Rand Corporation in Santa Monica with Richard Bellman, and taught mathematics at the College of Notre Dame in Belmont and at UCLA.  The Bella Manel Prize for outstanding graduate work by a woman or minority was established at NYU's Courant Institute in 1995.